  "text": "Grab your scarf — this one had EVERYTHING! Third-place play-off, 18 July 2026 — and A ten-goal bronze-medal classic ended with England on top — and a scoring record for Kylian Mbappé. Officially a match for third place; unofficially, one of the maddest games the tournament produced.\n\n3' — Declan Rice buried it, 0–1! 18' — Ezri Konsa lashed it home, 0–2! 38' — Bukayo Saka made no mistake, 0–3! 46' — Bukayo Saka found the net, 0–4! 48' — Kylian Mbappé smashed it in, 1–4! 54' — Bradley Barcola pounced, 2–4! 66' — Kylian Mbappé buried it, 3–4! 87' — Bukayo Saka from the spot lashed it home, 3–5! 96' — Ousmane Dembélé made no mistake, 4–5! 98' — Jude Bellingham found the net, 4–6!\n\nEngland raced into a four-goal lead through Declan Rice, Ezri Konsa and a Bukayo Saka double, and it looked like a rout. France roared back: Kylian Mbappé struck twice around a Bradley Barcola goal to close it to 3-4 and set nerves jangling. But Saka completed his hat-trick from the penalty spot, Ousmane Dembélé kept France alive, and Jude Bellingham had the very last word. Mbappé's double moved him above Lionel Messi as the World Cup's all-time leading scorer — yet it was England who went home with the bronze.\n\nFULL-TIME: France 4–6 England! England march on, France head home heartbroken — and here's the beautiful part: every goal, every minute you just heard is locked on-chain and verified by TxLINE. No hot air, no guesswork, just receipts. What. A. Game!",
